###clusterGeneration generates a number of files as its output for each run (.mem, .dat, .log etc.). After these files are generated, I push them up to github and read them back into R using the read.delim function (the file is a github raw URL). When I knit my RMarkdown document to HTML, it re-runs the clusterGeneration function and generates new files, rendering the github URLs with the old files useless. Here, Im trying to read the files using a local filepath to see if that solves the problem.

library(clusterGeneration)
## Loading required package: MASS
## Warning: package 'MASS' was built under R version 4.1.1
genRandomClust(3, sepVal = 0.01, numNonNoisy = 2, numNoisy = 0, numReplicate = 1, fileName = "scenx")

x_mem <- read.delim("/Users/emilyraney/Desktop/clustergen-master/clustergen/scenx_1.mem", header = FALSE, sep = " ")
